 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 6: EXTERNAL DOG-FOOD AS VALIDATION EXPERIMENT. The external dog-food becomes the experiment that validates the UAQ hypothesis: 'does a unified acquisition function converge faster than independent systems?' Protocol: (1) Initialize braid on external project with UAQ-enabled build. (2) Work 3 sessions, recording every recommendation event and its outcome. (3) Measure: (a) mean prediction error across ALL recommendation types, (b) F(S) convergence rate, (c) productive action rate (% of recommendations followed). (4) Compare to braid's own 36-session history where systems were independent. PREDICTION: UAQ should reach mean_error < 0.15 in 3 sessions (braid self-use took 35 sessions to reach 0.224 with fragmented calibration). FALSIFICATION: If mean_error is still above 0.20 after 3 sessions, the unified function isn't better than independent systems and the composition formula needs revision. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-019. This is the first empirical test of the three-primitive formalism (morphisms + reconciliation + acquisition function)."
